  "body": "hi, I want to invoke [TraceCall()](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/fb8ea5993f466bd398d33a42a8273c9fc2bf1fb6/eth/tracers/api.go#L726) from my go program, to call this method, I need to instantiate [tracers.Backend](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/fb8ea5993f466bd398d33a42a8273c9fc2bf1fb6/eth/tracers/api.go#L60) interface, and for that, I need to get [eth.EthAPIBackend](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/fb8ea5993f466bd398d33a42a8273c9fc2bf1fb6/eth/api_backend.go#L43) which is one of the implementations of it.\r\n\r\nbut there's no function like `NewEthAPIBackend()`, how can I get it?\r\n\r\nnow I have [ethclient.Client](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/fb8ea5993f466bd398d33a42a8273c9fc2bf1fb6/ethclient/ethclient.go#L35) in hand:\r\n\r\n```go\r\n\tif client, err = ethclient.DialContext(context.Background(), config.App.Eth.Node); err != nil {\r\n\t\tlogrus.Fatal( err)\r\n\t}\r\n```\r\n\r\nso back to the title, how do I instantiate [eth.EthAPIBackend](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/fb8ea5993f466bd398d33a42a8273c9fc2bf1fb6/eth/api_backend.go#L43)  from  [ethclient.Client](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/fb8ea5993f466bd398d33a42a8273c9fc2bf1fb6/ethclient/ethclient.go#L35)?",
