    "body": "It's not possible to do what you are asking, because the API Backend and ethclient are two different things.\r\nThe API Backend is the server side, ethclient is the client side.\r\n\r\nIf you want to invoke tracing methods on the server, you need to call them through RPC. \r\n\r\nCreate the RPC client like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nclient, err := rpc.DialContext(...)\r\nif err != nil {\r\n   // handle error\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow you can perform JSON-RPC calls:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntype traceResult struct{\r\n  Failed bool\r\n  Gas uint64\r\n  ReturnValue hexutil.Bytes\r\n  StructLogs []vm.StructLog\r\n}\r\n\r\nvar result traceResult\r\nerr := client.Call(&result, \"debug_traceCall\", ...)\r\nif err != nil {\r\n   // handle err\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
